+// Boundary character class for Bash matching: start-of-string OR any character
+// that can legitimately precede a path token. Critically includes quote chars
+// (single, double, backtick) and common shell delimiters so that
+// `rm '.swarm/evidence/4.4.json'`, `python -c "open('.swarm/evidence/…')"`,
+// and `cmd=.swarm/evidence/4.4.json` all match. Issue #862 follow-up.
+const BASH_PATH_BOUNDARY = `(?:^|[\\s/'"\`=:(,\\[{])`;
+
